☝🏼Here's how to attract clients who adore you in 3 easy steps! ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
STEP 1️⃣- Get clear on WHO you want to attract. What type of clients do you most enjoy working with? Consider their age, gender, occupation, interests and more.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
👉🏼The reason this step is so important is because when you market to one person--you’re creating clarity for your buyer.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
STEP 2️⃣- Understand their struggles and desires. What result is this person really craving? What would they do anything to avoid? ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
👉🏼If you're stumped, think about the FAQ you get. What struggles have you helped your patients overcome? What transformation were they able to experience as a result of working with you?⁠⠀
⁠⠀
STEP 3️⃣- Show your followers, subscribers, and patients that you really 'get them' by addressing their concerns in your posts, emails, and web copy. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀ 👉🏼The more clearly you can describe your ideal customers' pain points, the better you can position yourself as the solution to their problem. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
⁠⠀
What do you think? Would you add anything to this list?

Você conhece os 3 tipos oficiais de escrita?
.
Bom, eu vou citar quais são e pra quê cada uma delas servem. Mas também vou estar destacando o tipo de escrita que vou abordar mais profundamente aqui no meu perfil.
.
1. Publicidade: é o texto que traz uma escrita mais persuasiva, técnicas para converter o leitor à tornar um consumidor/participante do que está sendo oferecido.
.
2. Jornalismo: é uma forma de comunicar algo, informar de maneira imparcial, ou seja, neutro. É apresentar uma notícia, uma ideia, um produto.
.
3. Relações públicas (que carinhosamente apelidei de "copywriting para relacionamento"): é sobre esse tipo de escrita que mais vou trazer conteúdos para vocês. É uma escrita que tem como objetivo construir o posicionamento de uma marca, de uma ideia, de uma pessoa. Ela comunica os valores e o propósito do que está sendo informado e apresentado.
.
É muito importante dizer que nenhuma escrita é melhor do que a outra e nenhuma anula a outra.
.
O ideal é relacionar esses 3 elementos para construir sua marca e gerar os resultados desejados.
.
Se esse tipo de conhecimento é interessante para você e seu negócio comenta qual tipo de escrita faz mais sentido para usar em suas redes sociais: 1, 2 ou 3?
.
.
.

Não tenho tempo?

Hoje quantas horas você tem no seu dia? 24 horas certo? Todos temos as mesmas 24 horas.

Mesmo que não chegue as 24 horas, pois dormimos, saímos e etc... Possuímos teoricamente as mesmas 24 horas.

E porque então muitas pessoas quando recebem uma determinada tarefa, ou são convidadas para algo dizem “Não tenho Tempo”? E a resposta é simples “aquilo não faz parte da sua lista de prioridades”!. Quando a pessoa entende que aquilo não irá agregar valor para ela em determinada área, ou fara com que ela apenas perdera seu tempo.

Ela fala que não tem tempo!

Então uma dica legal é “PARE DE FALAR QUE NÃO TEM TEMPO”, pois tempo você tem, 24 horas.

Troque o “NÃO TENHO TEMPO” por “ISSO NÃO FAZ PARTE DA MINHA LISTA DE PRIORIDADES”. Com isso você deixara de mentir para si e mesmo, e conseguira dar foco no que realmente importa para você!

During the Middle Ages, pilgrims would end their pilgrimage to important cathedrals by walking a labyrinth. In the past 25 years labyrinths have become more popular than at any time in their 4,000-year history, says a leading authority.

OK, so during lockdown I have said:⁠
⁠
'I'll take advantage of my other half being home and work all the hours I can.'⁠
⁠
'I'll just work on my retainers and small contracts.'⁠
⁠
'I need work to keep me focused and motivated.'⁠
⁠
Pretty different takes on life, I know. But that's OK, this is a time for feeling unsettled and adapting to what feels right. But I do know now that the third of these is really true - extra time to worry is not what I need right now, so I'm leaning back into work and opening up space for two new clients next week.⁠
⁠
Why limit it to two? Because like many wise people have acknowledged, if there's any positive to be taken from this situation, it's learning to live at a pace that's right for us. Society has changed, but hopefully once this is over we can hang onto the good bits, and that's recognising that health and balance take priority over work. So yeah, just two clients.⁠
⁠
(And if you're thinking about maybe being one of them, send me a DM saying 'maybe', I'll chat you through everything you need to know about working with me to get that kick ass copy you need.)⁠

"THE MOST GIFTED HUMANS...⁠⠀
... are at their most creative when they cannot have their way, and must compensate for what they miss by realizing and cultivating their capacities and talents."⁠⠀
-Eric Hoffer⁠⠀
🔥⁠⠀
I came across this quote a few days ago as I was diving deep into research about creativity. I wanted to think through why I've never once questioned my creativity and figure-out-ability during what's going on in the world right now, and this really hit on what I BELIEVE TO MY VERY CORE.⁠⠀
✨⁠⠀
Constraints, crappy circumstances, confusing challenges STRENGTHEN our creativity, they don't constrict it.⁠⠀
⚡️⁠⠀
If you think about the phrase "get creative," we almost always use it in the midst of circumstances we can't control.⁠⠀
👏🏼⁠⠀
We say, "WELP, I GUESS WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO GET CREATIVE."⁠⠀
🤷🏼‍♀️⁠⠀
And, honestly? I've been repeating that sentence to myself daily as I roll up my sleeves to GET TO WORK.⁠⠀
💃🏼⁠⠀
Here's my encouragement to you today: Don't second guess your creativity. Stop saying you're STUCK. Sit down, take a deep breath, and see where your mind takes you. Your business and your life will thank you for it.⁠⠀
🙏🏼⁠⠀
How are you "getting creative" and cultivating your capacities and talents this week?

JAK OPALAĆ SIĘ W MAROKU?
Pytanie może dziwne na pierwszy rzut oka, ale przestaje takie być, gdy zagłębimy się w marokańską mentalność. Żeby była jasność, nie ma totalnie żadnego problemu, żeby wyjść na plażę w bikini. Nikt Cię nie skrytykuje, ani nie spróbuje ubrać. Maroko to kraj muzułmański, ale raczej z tych "luźniejszych". Więc na plażach spotkasz również Marokanki w bikini. I Marokanki w jelabach. Pełen przekrój. Zatem - na plaży w turystycznym mieście, na basenie, na tarasie riadu możesz bez problemu chodzić w bikini i korzystać z afrykańskiego słońca. Gorzej, gdy tak jak ja teraz, mieszkasz wśród Marokańczyków. W 4-piętrowym bloku, gdzie każdy ma dostęp do tarasu na dachu, który to taras służy przede wszystkim do suszenia prania. Nie do grillowania, a już na pewno nie do opalania się w bikini. Więc cierpię. I kombinuję. Biorę kocyk, ubieram się w długą spódnicę, luźną koszulkę na ramiączkach, zarzucam na ramiona chustę. Rozkładam się za ścianą, żeby nikogo nie spotkać. I nasłuchuję, czy nikt nie idzie 😅 ja nie mam problemu, żeby mnie ktoś zobaczył, ale dla ludzi tutaj, szczególnie mężczyzn, zobaczenie nagle kobiety odsłaniającej sporo ciała jest bardzo krępujące. Więc żeby uszanować ich kulturę, a jednocześnie nie płakać, że nic nie mam z tego słońca, odsłaniam nogi, dekolt i ramiona, a gdy słyszę, że ktoś się zbliża, narzucam spódnicę i chustę. Taka sytuacja 😅
Zdarzyło mi się, że napatoczył się na mnie mężczyzna, zanim zarzuciłam się chustą. Zaczął mnie przepraszać ze spuszczonym wzrokiem. A tak naprawdę to ja czułam, że powinnam przeprosić jego, bo to ja wykraczam poza ramy tutejszej kultury. W każdym razie chyba się lubimy z sąsiadami 😉
.
.
.

I want to share with you a tip I learned when I attended an awesome and ultra nerdy copywriting webinar last week.

It's something you can easily use in content or sales copy to sell your offer: "The Damaging Admission." Honestly, this blew my mind. But it makes so much sense.

The damaging admission is when you admit an actual flaw of your offer. We're not talking about hyperbole here. You can't say, "Oh, well, my online course isn't going to bring world peace." Um. Yeah, no sh*t it isn't.

The damaging admission needs to be a real flaw of your program, followed by a real quality of your program.

Why? Because admitting a real flaw establishes trust. It tells your customer, hey, we're not here to dupe you, but we ARE here to do xyz.

Because here's the thing, your customer will always have a doubt and your copy's job is to coach them through the decision-making process. The damaging admission helps them make that decision.

So, next time you're writing some copy, or you're on a sales call, remember the damaging admission. It might make all the difference.
.
.
